<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,1767,2025]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,498,1844,1870]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Diagnostic description.</emphasis>
Body light reddish brown, shining. Larger than 
<taxonomicName box="[1174,1289,1845,1870]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kiseri">
<emphasis box="[1174,1289,1845,1870]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">H. kiseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, length of pronotum+elytra = 2.7–2.8 mm (males). Head irregularly punctate. Pronotum widest near middle, sides rounded, basal angles obtusely rounded; ratio length:width = 1:1.4; finely punctate with faint reticulate microsculpture. Elytra wider than pronotum, of medium length, ratio length:width = 1:0.7; stria 1 clearly impressed, remaining striae punctate, interval punctures similar to strial punctures, transverse strioles present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,152,448]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
Antennal club (
<figureCitation box="[331,417,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–54" captionStartId="23.[151,271,805,829]" captionTargetBox="[282,1316,200,773]" captionTargetId="figure-411@23.[272,1316,194,781]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 52–54. Hydnobius acarinus. 52. Right antenna, dorsal view. 53. Male right metafemur and metatibia. 54. Aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 54), 0.4 mm (Fig. 52), 0.5 mm (Fig. 53)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310923/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
) moderately slender, ratio club width:length = 1:3.4; width ratio of antennomeres 7:8:9 = 1.3:1:1.7. Right mandible bidentate, with a submedian tooth; left mandible with tooth on apical one-half of inner margin. Mesoventrite lacking a median longitudinal carina (diagnostic character for separating this species from 
<taxonomicName box="[306,406,268,293]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Hydnobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kiseri">
<emphasis box="[306,406,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">H. kiseri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Profemur and mesofemur of male unarmed; male metafemur (
<figureCitation box="[1152,1236,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–54" captionStartId="23.[151,271,805,829]" captionTargetBox="[282,1316,200,773]" captionTargetId="figure-411@23.[272,1316,194,781]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 52–54. Hydnobius acarinus. 52. Right antenna, dorsal view. 53. Male right metafemur and metatibia. 54. Aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 54), 0.4 mm (Fig. 52), 0.5 mm (Fig. 53)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310923/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
) with large tooth before apex of posterior margin. Male protibia widened apically; mesotibia with inner margin weakly sinuate, lobed at apex; metatibia (
<figureCitation box="[454,542,345,371]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–54" captionStartId="23.[151,271,805,829]" captionTargetBox="[282,1316,200,773]" captionTargetId="figure-411@23.[272,1316,194,781]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 52–54. Hydnobius acarinus. 52. Right antenna, dorsal view. 53. Male right metafemur and metatibia. 54. Aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 54), 0.4 mm (Fig. 52), 0.5 mm (Fig. 53)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310923/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
) angulate on inner margin near basal one-third, apical two-thirds widened. All tibiae spinose on outer margin. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[582,653,383,409]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Male.</emphasis>
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[799,887,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURES 52–54" captionStartId="23.[151,271,805,829]" captionTargetBox="[282,1316,200,773]" captionTargetId="figure-411@23.[272,1316,194,781]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 52–54. Hydnobius acarinus. 52. Right antenna, dorsal view. 53. Male right metafemur and metatibia. 54. Aedeagus, dorsal view. Scale bar = 0.3 mm (Fig. 54), 0.4 mm (Fig. 52), 0.5 mm (Fig. 53)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5310923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5310923/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
) with median lobe broad, narrowing to acute apex. Parameres narrow, outwardly curved, with two apical setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[927,1026,422,448]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
